                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Word of Terris is a necro charm that's 65th level but it can't charm as high level stuff as CoD can.  In Tactics, a necro friend of mine can't charm War Wraiths and I can.  Plus, they can only charm undead mobs.  
<br />

<br />
Their max duration is 20.5 minutes on it, but it seems to last an average of 20 seconds if I don't tash the mob first for him.  Read some necro boards about it, that's the norm rather than the exception.
<br />

<br />
As for druids, their charm spell is 63rd level.  It also has a 20.5 minute max duration but it doesn't charm as high level mobs as CoD does.  Druids have a MR debuff at least, something Necro's don't have, that lasts, hilariously enough, 20.5 minutes.  It only lowers MR by 20 though and doesn't stack with Tash.  (My druid bot has it.)
<br />

<br />
So both classes do have a max duration 20.5 minute charm but it doesn't last 20.5 minutes on average.  They can't get TD, have either no MR debuff or a crappy one, and they can only charm low level very specific creatures whereas we can charm almost anything, and higher level, WITH an MR debuff that's second to none.
<br />

<br />
Edit:  Forgot to mention mages but their charm is also 20.5 minutes, they can cast Malosinia which lowers MR by 70, but the only zone they're effective in is BoT that I'm aware of, and some LDoN's, because they can only charm summoned creatures and the Elementals in BoT are summoned.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
