                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">max duration charm (excluding Dire charm) for enchanters is 7.5 minutes, without early breaks
<br />
max duration charm for necros and mages is 20 minutes, without early breaks 
<br />
the TD aa is to prevents early breaks.  So spend your aa in TD3 and you still cannot outcharm these guys on a good day with a RNG. 
<br />
We are talking about our role and where we are headed. We are talking about being a needed class. We are a buffing class, make no mistake.  I knew that when I rolled up my character.  There are other classes that are considered buffing classes as well.  At 65 level (pre GoD), we should get more for our rune turn in than 2 group buffs and an illusion.  Personally, I would like the 20 minute charm.  Wizards get a 65 nuke, shamans get a 65 DoT, etc etc.  
<br />
As it stands now, enchanters have to overplay their class.  There's nothing wrong with that, I personally enjoy it.  I like our gimp nukes with an ID4 item, I like to buff, to debuff, to mezz, to charm, "rune-style" healing.  It's fun.  I does seem to me, however, that the more we overplay the class, the more the developers underplay it.  Making full use of a classes abilities is not an exploit.  
<br />
I too, would like to see the reaction of the warriors if their defensive aa did not work in a particular zone, or a MoB was untargetable by melee because they were 100% melee resistant.  I would like to see the clerics in a zone where CH was not an option, because their complete heal was resisted due to the zone they were in.  
<br />
From early on, there have existed 100% MR mobs, unmezzable mobs, uncharmable mobs, etc.  I know that most of the people reading this post work around it daily.  It makes us more creative problem solvers, better gamers.  If playing this class were easy, everyone would do it.  However, when I look at other classes abilities, spell lists, and the recent addition of combat abilities, it seems like the other classes are getting stronger, while we are, at the very least, staying exactly the same.
<br />
  I think the enchanter class is out of balance with the other classes in game.  I would like that to change. We lost the reduce stamina line.  Other classes got some sort of vision enhancement (infravision?), which we already had. <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> With each update, I see this class losing more and gaining less.  I do not begrudge the other classes for their upgrades.  But at 65 level 2 group buffs and an illusion says a lot to me.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
